article.description: — Ryan Moffatt had 14 points to lead five Colgate players in double figures as the Raiders romped past Holy Cross 95-55 on Saturday.
article.headline: Moffatt, Ferguson lead Colgate over Holy Cross 95-55
article.linkText: Moffatt, Ferguson lead Colgate over Holy Cross 95-55
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- — Ryan Moffatt had 14 points to lead five Colgate players in double figures as the Raiders romped past Holy Cross 95-55 on Saturday. Jack Ferguson added 13 points for the Raiders. Keegan Records chipped in 12, Oliver Lynch-Daniels scored 11 as did Nelly Cummings. Matt Faw had 14 points, 11 rebounds and four blocks for the Crusaders (2-3, 2/3 Patriot League). Gerrale Gates added 11 points. The two teams play each other again Sunday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
